§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬matrix exponential❭ of a real matrix $M ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$
    is the matrix
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ I + M + \frac{M^2}{2!} + \frac{M^3}{3!} + ⋯. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ It is a (nontrivial) fact that this (matrix) power series
    converges for all $M ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$. ⦉
